      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, oakmont definitely feels classic. but i'm worried about it sounding a bit... i don't know, stagnant? like it's just old people in old houses. \n\nthe meridian district (option 2) seems like it could also work for high-end clients who want that 'sophisticated global citizen' vibe. why wouldn't that count as prestigious? isn't international culture and high-end art also a sign of refinement?",
